## 🐛 Bug Report

`CellHyperlinkValue` text property is declared as `string` but using the lib i had to handle the case where it was a `RichText[]`

https://github.com/exceljs/exceljs/blob/5bed18b45e824f409b08456b59b87430ded023ab/index.d.ts#L345

Lib version: 4.4.0

## Steps To Reproduce

File with Hiperlink with rich text:

[wrong_type_test.xlsx](https://github.com/user-attachments/files/22540641/wrong_type_test.xlsx)


```javascript

const wb = new ExcelJS.Workbook();
wb  = await workbook.xlsx.load(buffer);
const cellValue = wb.getWorkSheet(1).getRow(2).getCell(1).value

expect('hyperlink' in cellValue).to.equal(true);
expect('text' in cellValue).to.equal(true);
expect(typeof  cellValue.text).to.equal('string'); // ERROR

```

## The expected behaviour:

Update index.d.ts to have the proper types.


```javascript
HyperlinkCellValue {
  hyperlink: string;
  text: string|RichText[];
}

```
